<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="279" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,222,751]" pageId="6" pageNumber="279">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,474,499]" pageId="6" pageNumber="279">Remarks.</emphasis>
The material examined from 
<collectingCountry box="[675,812,475,499]" name="Hong Kong" pageId="6" pageNumber="279">Hong Kong</collectingCountry>
and south 
<collectingCountry box="[950,1017,474,499]" name="China" pageId="6" pageNumber="279">China</collectingCountry>
is very constant in markings, with prothorax entirely brown and no pale stripe on the metepisternum. The sizes of all examined Chinese specimens fall in the ranges given for males by 
<bibRefCitation author="Wilson" box="[566,732,546,571]" pageId="6" pageNumber="279" refString="Wilson, K. D. P. (1997) The Platystictidae of Hong Kong and Guandong, with descriptions of a new genus and two new species. Odonatologica, 26 (1), 53 - 63." type="journal article" year="1997">Wilson (1997)</bibRefCitation>
: abdomen plus appendages 
<quantity box="[1046,1168,546,571]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.35" metricValueMax="3.6" metricValueMin="3.1" pageId="6" pageNumber="279" unit="mm" value="33.5" valueMax="36.0" valueMin="31.0">31–36 mm</quantity>
and Hw 
<quantity box="[1271,1395,546,571]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="2.1" pageId="6" pageNumber="279" unit="mm" value="23.0" valueMax="25.0" valueMin="21.0">21–25 mm</quantity>
. Of the specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[391,489,582,607]" name="Vietnam" pageId="6" pageNumber="279">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
, that from Tay Thien also has an entirely brown prothorax and no stripe on the metepisternum, but those from Ba Vi have large yellowish lateral marks on the anterior pronotal lobe. The specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[336,431,654,679]" name="Vietnam" pageId="6" pageNumber="279">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
are larger than those from 
<collectingCountry box="[735,806,654,679]" name="China" pageId="6" pageNumber="279">China</collectingCountry>
: Tay Thien male with abdomen plus anal appendages ca 
<quantity box="[151,257,690,715]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.75" pageId="6" pageNumber="279" unit="mm" value="37.5">37.5 mm</quantity>
, Hw 
<quantity box="[326,433,690,715]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.65" pageId="6" pageNumber="279" unit="mm" value="26.5">26.5 mm</quantity>
; Ba Vi males with abdomen plus anal appendages 
<quantity box="[1040,1189,690,715]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.225" metricValueMax="4.25" metricValueMin="4.2" pageId="6" pageNumber="279" unit="mm" value="42.25" valueMax="42.5" valueMin="42.0">42–42.5 mm</quantity>
, Hw 
<quantity box="[1257,1385,690,715]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.65" metricValueMax="2.8" metricValueMin="2.5" pageId="6" pageNumber="279" unit="mm" value="26.5" valueMax="28.0" valueMin="25.0">25–28 mm</quantity>
. All examined specimens have a robust subbasal spur on the paraprocts, clearly visible even in lateral view.
</paragraph>
